[{"location":"pages/content/#This-is-where-the-documentation-begins...","page":"Content","title":"This is where the documentation begins...","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#*It's-just-a-template,-but-documentation-will-be-here-soon.*","page":"Home","title":"It's just a template, but documentation will be here soon.","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#Quickstart","page":"Home","title":"Quickstart","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"A standard julia guide that demonstrates the main cases of working with documenting a package. Here is the basic syntax for working with docstrings, style guide and tips. A more detailed guide to working with the documenter is shown here.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Below is a simple example of using docstring:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"\\\"\\\"\\\"\n    bar(x[, y])\n\nCompute the Bar index between `x` and `y`.\n\nIf `y` is unspecified, compute the Bar index between all pairs of columns of `x`.\n\n# Examples\n\n```julia-repl\njulia> bar([1, 2], [1, 2])\n1\n```\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\nfunction bar(x, y) ...","category":"page"},{"location":"#Local-documentation-build","page":"Home","title":"Local documentation build","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"If you want to build the documentation locally, you need to run the command julia --project docs/make.jl in the root of the package directory.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Documenantion-file-structure","page":"Home","title":"Documenantion file structure","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Let's go through the main documentation files and folders.","category":"page"},{"location":"#docs/make.jl","page":"Home","title":"docs/make.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This file contains the makedocs method, which builds the documentation. Let's look at a few important keywords you might need:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"pages can be use to specify a hierarchical page structure, and the order in which the pages appear in the navigation of the rendered output. If omitted, Documenter will automatically generate a flat list of pages based on the files present in the source directory.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"pages = [\n    \"Overview\" => \"index.md\",\n    \"tutorial.md\",\n    \"Tutorial\" => [\n        \"tutorial/introduction.md\",\n        \"Advanced\" => \"tutorial/features.md\",\n    ],\n    \"apireference.md\",\n]","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"assets: For the logo, Documenter checks for the existence of assets/logo.{svg,png,webp,gif,jpg,jpeg}, in this order. The first one it finds gets displayed at the top of the navigation sidebar. It will also check for assets/logo-dark.{svg,png,webp,gif,jpg,jpeg} and use that for dark themes. For the favicon, Documenter checks for the existence of assets/favicon.ico.\nsidebar_sitename determines whether the site name is shown in the sidebar or not. Setting it to false can be useful when the logo already contains the name of the package. Defaults to true.","category":"page"},{"location":"#docs/src/index.md","page":"Home","title":"docs/src/index.md","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"If you use Documenter's default HTML output the name index.md is mandatory. This file will be the main page of the rendered HTML documentation.","category":"page"},{"location":"#docs/src/pages/","page":"Home","title":"docs/src/pages/","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"All your markdown documentation files will be located here.","category":"page"},{"location":"#docs/src/assets/","page":"Home","title":"docs/src/assets/","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This is where all the resources you need for documentation are located, inlcuding logo and favicon. See also add logo.","category":"page"}]
